<Link id="l00658" /><CodeLine lineNumber="658"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Looks at a token type and creates the relevant operand</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00661" /><CodeLine lineNumber="661"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> XtensaAsmParser::parseOperand(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a61e27c75c3334cffa54c44c02077da1e">OperandVector</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/mirnamerpass-cpp/#a05e4be4ec3e2c3587dda0e376bb6822c">Operands</a>, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> Mnemonic,</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00663" /><CodeLine lineNumber="663"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Check if the current operand has a custom associated parser, if so, try to</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00664" /><CodeLine lineNumber="664"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// custom parse the operand, or fallback to the general approach.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00665" /><CodeLine lineNumber="665"><Highlight kind="normal">  ParseStatus Res = MatchOperandParserImpl(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/mirnamerpass-cpp/#a05e4be4ec3e2c3587dda0e376bb6822c">Operands</a>, Mnemonic);</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00668" /><CodeLine lineNumber="668"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00669" /><CodeLine lineNumber="669"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If there wasn&#39;t a custom match, try the generic matcher below. Otherwise,</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
